nder-neutral restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true},{"name":"Transgender safespace","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Serena Raynard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVh-5WpYJkp9e72wEtqIKVMIQgsjyC0-RP5kFEv7wbjuYnAdbBY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had such a great experience at ATX Family Dental. I came in with pain from previous dental work done elsewhere, and the dentist took the time to really listen and explain what was going on. He was honest, conservative, and didn’t rush me into unnecessary treatment. The whole team was kind, thorough, and made me feel comfortable right away. I finally feel like I’m in good hands, highly recommend!!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3f8sQHzu9XP7UNjXLfCSrt9x6ANJ3VwDcNpqx29cJ5Vfl3IH4bIPLgJHlS7ISlOTZlvLM40XgtFuKUcvOrcnDJa7ibR4DCCFDrnw9oKvFsDTfcKhxA_RXiwiQ8voh2qOL3u4eeIdIyMPYh=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1ej4RtxFULIQVfDhOzf_SZb8YpWphJnqNshnSQyTiYMqjq4iGuPhajF1eNZodD-QiKxvZ3LcJFR7n_xto8CMHqHO3gadPqInJHwhezK2JU-pKvArUwXhQU8-AdJOcWJfjj517CmVLyans=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn32_z_TfCtuwC5Kj80tJLMCeBeMPkt0LFAeKY1agioUKCaPRw0ap-E7HmC4E9YlIbKKtHAfzI_cu383Uf8a5vlUT0bJoJYVr81JEB7oPmCrofxLXngsdy2uY409Ah4BcflOuAac17JCj9FU=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-13"},{"Name":"Anais Pegias","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIs2S8oVkIMj8mAHXV5GF7ONBm3SPDyZD6cbXlIrDASY4hFeA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had my first visit at ATX Family Dental today for a filling after deciding to switch from my previous dental practice, which had been a really bad experience. I am so glad I made the change.\n\nAmanda did an incredible job on my filling. She is extremely skilled, gentle, and made the whole process feel easy and smooth.\n\nMy assistant Kirsten was also wonderful and made me feel very relaxed throughout the appointment.\n\nThe whole team was professional and welcoming, and the experience was smooth from start to finish. I would absolutely recommend ATX Family Dental to anyone looking for a great dentist in Austin.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rachel Kohlman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVXSC_RH8YGmPHMyZg6oVQR2YAHej4g37DKidZeSlphWrUKA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If I could give ATX Family Dental six stars, I would. This was my first dental experience in Downtown Austin and I cannot say enough great things about this practice. The office is beautiful and bright and colorful, the people are incredibly kind and bubbly, the dental cleaning and exam were super professional. I had a few dental concerns and was walked through all of the options possible, many of which have never been a possibility at other dentists.\n\nDr. Adam and his wife have done a fabulous job with their practice, and it feels like way more than a local family practice. The only way I will ever get a new dentist is if I leave Austin, and even then, flights aren’t that expensive.😂\n\nI love you guys already @ ATX Family Dental!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1Pkz6TLH5Ukjj_iAUhuQy8PeSqzirPXX1kT49QhzOItbHbmtDd9GsUUm7Rz4OmCrL4EoVdjHuP9lANKoJEIuGmlQVTAoRzVmhNjstneyJS0SGlvuUWkYTnRhhK7E35yuUnaGjrOc6Ps1bg=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-25"},{"Name":"K L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKmWBfYQfVQw1xdppjU3V5T1qesG_tluM8yTKEKa04DRoBFA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"ATX Family Dental's Wellness Plan saved me when I found out my employer's dental insurance wasn't accepted by any dental offices and my previous dentist kept pushing my appointment months out. I was able to sign up for the plan and be seen within 2 days of making the change.\n\nWhen I arrived, parking was simple and the office was gorgeous! Everyone was so nice. Then I saw the technology. Ever had the goopy, nasty impressions on your teeth? ATX Family Dental said NO MORE! They have a machine that takes 1,000s of photos per second and builds a model of your mouth. They also had TVs on the ceiling so I got to watch Planet Earth while my teeth were cleaned. When I was done, they literally gave me a gold star sticker for taking care of my teeth. I'm an adult and I don't think we get NEARLY enough stickers anymore, so that was a very pleasant surprise!\n\nI am happy to say that after feeling lost and forgotten with my previous dentist, I now LOVE my dentist! I have cancelled my insurance and will go to ATX Family Dental from now on!\n\nKeep up the great work and see you in 6 months! :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Silas Demetriou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIil8Yr4QzPN-SS8xUdXVScw1M1CNr15KOQTjMkiUm_eEtq=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If we’re being real…nobody likes going to the dentist. But ATX Family Dental completely changed the experience for me.\n\nFirst off, the space is chic, modern, and actually feels intentional. Not sterile and cold , but stylish and welcoming. The waiting room is super cute and thoughtfully designed, which already makes you feel more relaxed walking in.\n\nEvery treatment room has a TV on the ceiling (because seriously… why do dentists put them on the wall where you can’t even see them while laying back?). And yes — they give you the remote. Full control. As they should.\n\nThey also give you these cool heart-eye sunglasses while they work on you, which is such a small but fun touch that makes everything feel less clinical and more comfortable.\n\nBeyond the aesthetics though — the environment felt inclusive and diverse. I felt safe in more ways than one, and that matters. A lot. 🏳️‍🌈\n\nIf you’re in Austin and have been putting off a dentist visit, this might be the place that changes your mind.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shauna Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUungmW525k1D6zuEy5bCbeSiMKRfvDlAfHOMQ34_3NKnUnRw90=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came to ATX Family Dental based on recommendations from two friends I trust.  I had my first cleaning and exam with Dr. Adam a couple of weeks ago and I went back the following week for specific work, also with Dr. Adam.  For a person who isn't easily satisfied in a dentist's office, I am highly satisfied with ATX Family Dental, so far.  My experiences both times had consistency from the front desk to the exam room.  People here make eye contact with you, communicate what to expect with clarity- from the front desk, to the waiting room, to the dental chair.  I also like that they seek further clarity with me by asking if I have questions at each transition.\nThe friends who recommended Dr. Adam's office know my back story.  Without sharing all the details, I had terrible dental experiences with two dentists many years ago.  I'm not proud to say it, but for 14 years, I became dentist avoidant.  Fortunately, I overcame my fears, but suffice it to say, I look for traits that go beyond framed credentials.  I'm looking for professionalism and interpersonal skills that signal the people I'm going to for my dental care are trustworthy.  That criteria will not be the same for everyone.  So far, Dr. Adam and his team are ticking all the right boxes.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX15ahnIceouloMc6ePUEUJRTXNlrsgTtadQlfNxLXaOdJ0CBxn=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Would you believe me if I said I kinda look forward to going to the dentist now?\n\nLike many people, I used to dread dental appointments after a few not-so-great experiences and even delayed care because of it. ATX Family Dental completely changed that. Every team member leads with kindness, respect, and empathy. They take the time to clearly explain your care plan, answer all your questions, and never pressure you into optional or elective treatments. It’s a judgment-free zone! They manage to bring professionalism and humor into the experience, even though laughing with dental tools in your mouth can be tricky.  They all seem to genuinely enjoy their jobs and working together.. idk, It’s just a good time! I never thought I would write a review for a dental office, but here we are. Big fan. Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Byron Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIstocS3QUxXsmeiLqrlo9D7xtqi5Xz1zxX8X_KPJ_56rr1DQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent experience at ATX Family Dental. Sandy and Dr. Adam Gutwein were incredibly attentive, efficient, and welcoming. You can tell they truly care about their patients and take pride in what they do. The office is modern, clean, and very well run.\n\nAfter searching around, I’ve officially found my dentist in Austin.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
