,"image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=wcP83eQsLFVcxIWI3HcDHQ\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=229.29869\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://austinprimarydental.com/contact-us/?utm_source=GMB\u0026utm_medium=organic\u0026utm_campaign=DevOptimization\u0026utm_content=AppointmentRequest","source":"austinprimarydental.com"},{"link":"https://flexbook.me/apd?rwg_token=AFd1xnE2iCYH9O-iJTT917fcNX9Eay2E9lkOgLQ0utV8X1vA-gVrzVK8bLyVCcWnXD940rk69QQHIVlfZvsWM0ZRys0gJ4OPIw%3D%3D","source":"flexbook.me"}],"menu":{"link":"/url?q=http://places.singleplatform.com/austin-primary-dental/menu%3Fref%3Dgoogle\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwiAx5OzkcuUAxXFETQIHcDWMJgQqRkIHSgQ\u0026usg=AOvVaw3b3aDWbX8E2hCK5chTg34R","source":"places.singleplatform.com"},"owner":{"id":"106306924992624841197","name":"Austin Primary Dental (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106306924992624841197"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Garrison Park","street":"6700 West Gate Blvd STE 103","city":"Austin","postal_code":"78745","state":"Texas","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Victoria","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8WAwmmuHqftun3h8Vnxb44ZfueZ30qHn0fDx5BP_TwMKCzC0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I, like many others, detest going to the dentist. However, my experience here has been incredibly positive. The service is exceptional, and the staff is incredibly kind and knowledgeable. When I entered the office, I was greeted with warm smiles, and my cleaning left me feeling refreshed, not sore or prodded. The dentist herself is incredibly kind and knowledgeable. She came in to check me out, and I could tell she truly understood her work. Overall, I had a fantastic experience and would highly recommend this office to anyone seeking dental care.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Slappy Chicken","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfu3uHaJUUc9O02-DqgHhMT3rDqws1illosO0z6UFlVb4vcclSHg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re an American like me, you probably have spent your wad on medical coverage which leaves little for dental coverage. That’s ok because the deep cleaning prices are fair here at only $1,000. This is actually fair for Austin TX. Luckily I only spend $1,500 a month/$18,000 a year for me and my wife’s medical coverage.  That’s why it was so easy to find the extra $1,000 laying around.  It’s great to finally be rich enough to get medical care after deciding to start a small business and working more than I’ve ever worked. Every day. Every weekend for years. Some times working over 200 days straight without any time off. I feel so lucky to be in this position to get my teeth cleaned.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0_37OR8JfdHl9Igp2RAgOBm3RAKFINj0ztYg2a5Lct1N8SF7uurJWBb5K0-QP60oqEPUUtmX1K4HpPEaT4DMF4RnhJBY589Wd0QOE5I3XS_tkqn1pqs0QR8QiBqXcSN8e2Aez0MIx1P-45=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-1"},{"Name":"Sumitha Tharasingh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRsDxEnbyiSZcw7OxUzk45hqnFJCPmapjrxe9lG7vLfHUoKg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Rupa Rajanna has been my dentist for the last two years. I had stopped going to dentist during Covid and had some serious work to be done. Dr. Rupa’s office was responsive in getting me in and Dr. Rajanna took care of my needs quickly and professionally. She has outstanding knowledge and fine mirror skills. She was thorough in her evaluation and ensured I am comfortable throughout the procedures and ensured work was done per my satisfaction. Now my entire family sees her for dental care. I’d recommend Austin Primary Dental to any one needing dental care.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Izabel Brelage","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpqAjQu7IJ1Ghx5Nm5OfbawaMsENCozZ6-hAijv5w7JkN7TciV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"LOVE LOVE this dentist!! Staff is super friendly and I'm not a huge fan of teeth cleaning (who is??) but I felt super comfortable the whole time. The doctor was very professional and overall a very nice experience, 10/10 would recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Grecia Helena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZyhUUrcslJpNuLL2rhvPR_CVJBX87AdB61ZWFVdbILKReWa4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"About a month ago I came here for a cleaning, I heard on their speakers the commercial about Immigrants going back to their country (maybe the radio, so I ignored it)\n\nA few weeks later I came here to bring my sister, and I see Sydney Sweenie magazine, front and center. (again maybe they just get it in the mail, I didn’t assume anything) it wasn’t until the receptionist turned on the tv, struggled with it for about 5 minutes and CHOSE Fox News to play on full blast, talking about “our president is saving Venezuela” (mind you it’s ONLY me and her in the waiting area at this point) so I asked her to turn it off which she did. If we’re going to push a political agenda, why is it a hateful one? this was sketchy thing number three, so I decided I didn’t want to be here.\n\nLater my sister comes out and they had failed to tell  her that her process was TWO PARTS until they were finished with part one. That they needed to send off a crown to the lab, so she had a temporary crown for two whole weeks. So after I had decided to not return here, we HAD to come back. I needed the same procedure and found that other dentist practices can do it in one sitting.  (Austin modern dentistry, down the road, does the root canal crowns in office same day and it’s about the same price I went to them a day after the Fox News incident for my own crown and everything was good)\n\nSafe to say I did not make my next cleaning appointment here and will not return.\nIf you don’t mind a place with racist undertones then the staff is pretty friendly. They’re also friendly at Austin Modern Dentistry, and there’s no weird commercials, or conservative news outlets (:","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rohit Ranganath","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOCICmW4umvDO4Fwm8ZsxHWX1Ve4X1AXTs47-7JuGjlAiaFfL7Rw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great experience at this Austin dental clinic! The staff was friendly, the checkup and cleaning were thorough, and everything was handled professionally. Dr. Rupa Rajanna was especially kind and clear in explaining next steps for my dental health. Highly recommend for quality care in Austin!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marisa Silva","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKqISU83ZPCwQkgA479sKAsqyIBs7u9WTfF87ebabVa0W4e8A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have only been here a few times in the past 4 years, because I live out of state and then was trying to save money. But now I have returned with alot more work to do on maintaining my teeth help. I have had positive experience with everyone that works there doing their work and their role very well to help me, including Dr. Rupa Rajanna, they are consistent and approach me with truth, dental education, and realness. I have only had teeth cleaning and fillings. I also have gotten a lot of great advice with help with enamel loss that occurred after i drank acidic beverages consistently for a few years, and the dental hygienist helped reveal to me that this is what was happening.  And gave my alot of great advice to assist me in my personal habits. Thanks so much.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jocelyn Knezevich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnUfKFuj8A1rYij7nU0qSgIC1zmBoURPmghaN15dA4Y1MjfZ32ag=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been coming to Dr. Rajanna's for a while and always have a good experience. Everyone is friendly, gentle, and professional, and the office is clean and well run. I always feel well taken care of.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
