cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"S. Marshall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQY1NF4wbnOKclsbGvWUJy3e8I7vSCoyWwlQePTMzp31XtXQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The medical staff are first- rate.  My exam was thorough and staff communicated procedures and findings.  The receptionist was the only negative experience: no greeting, no please or thank-you— a real pickle.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dayna Prather","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLyB7O5V5uZHFMaTC-dKg2rEii7p6Akg3FQ4ud10Q--pRpDZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Swish Dental has state of the art equipment.  The facilities are very modern, the staff is friendly, and they make you feel at home.  Everything is handled directly with your phone,.from check in to signature on forms.  I also appreciate the fact that they tell you your cost for services, upfront. No surprises, at all.  Today, I had my regular dental cleaning, and ordered a night guard.  The fitting was super easy, they use the iTero scan to make a 3D model of your teeth and bite.   I will definitely be returning to this place for my regular cleanings and any other work I need done.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Issac Flores","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIbf5N_m3YbLqMWaxyJsF84luDlGH6cClWci4uuXcUTjMJp=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Marmurek is an absolute gem! She makes going to the dentist something I actually don’t dread anymore. Her care, skill, and kindness speak for themselves. Don’t hesitate to book with her! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brittany H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLLsmbrhU6w43alIVUhQGx7Me7Vps7EZdgnd_KO5XOZT2wWBXn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a severe mouth abscess everywhere I called the appointments where weeks or months out. Swish got me in for a same day exam and same day extraction. Thank you so much this has been an ongoing problem for me for the last 5 months and now I'm finally getting relief.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rosalinda","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbqQXZYlgBsZX1nGDJ3d0dl0wMO7RMpMO6Gz6JEuRr2jXeTFw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Brought my daughter here for her first ever dentist visit! Cute clean space, but for having “family” in the name I didn’t notice anything welcoming for children. They had TVs in front of the chairs but nothing playing. Thankful my daughter was open to her first experience, was just expecting more inviting for her age. The staff in the back were friendly and the doctor provided some good suggestions.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn239YJP4nJCUvGgT5MUYoEN8RRUUOX_4B3UbOj71yvetrW5eaioq1vlkRmKY8oIK0QgS7ThoBje2TpXm2E8Rtjm3SBMtBviGjWYr57i-8OcoOjoWqF1EGv8KIVN2ap2pqzZMmQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3gJiVYCKkFTq1tMILa6CbWU0fx-vF1DgHgtpH7bY-Sg98RQZN8oKqe5aITJnLtM3SX2s4t8qGTlg9mAzvoB6naUWvspdyKi0RwKj2XW8PlOe9TwEuq34mGzHTZBltHZnc_w0ROYg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1M1Js7tm5WGL9nLp287h059jWWMTX_Nci6VGn08dKVtbl9BVqf5I8RjkOcSvLWrkFX2DMnGkf4VUeaPvb3ima9FhbosbMDR690UdYCy70ph9q-rv7FoCqNIksJvIDhqlnWnUGm=k-no"],"When":"2025-3-18"},{"Name":"Madeline Campbell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZT7sXsYrH8sIpHp7RGkj1aHi2Mau7IoEj9tydpBlStORc1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I am so tired of private equity owned dental practices who put profit above anything else. Swish dental performs unnecessary services just to send a massive bill for a normal cleaning and see if your insurance will pay. You won't have to pay, but this model is greedy and increases the cost of healthcare for everyone.\n\nSwish is constantly trying to upsell you--they were visibly upset when I said I would prefer to get Invisalign done with an actual orthodontist, which they did not have on staff.\n\nThey did not let me skip my yearly screening x-rays even though I was pregnant, which was against the recommendations of my OBGYN. Note I have never had a cavity, was not having any pain/issues, and had normal x-rays at their practice a year earlier.\n\nWhen I finally got fed up enough and decided to move dental practices, they never sent me my records despite three phone calls (where I spoke to an associate each time) and one email.\n\nJust avoid this place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amy Marton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUMROVAgtMTDT8s9Fn4m-G-WEuzala-JecEl1bKGMzvevEIUmHCw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"High tech equipment doesn’t make up for fraudulent billing and terrible customer service.\n\nThey will try to apply a fluoride treatment at an additional $35 cost without making you aware of the cost beforehand. I only knew to decline the treatment and additional charge because a friend told me to expect it. Despite declining the treatment, they billed my insurance for it anyway. How convenient for them. How could it cost the customer $35 when they’re also billing for insurance and getting it covered? Be aware also that unless you pressure them into it, they will not actually clean your teeth on your first visit. They will take a bunch of X-rays you don’t need so they can charge for them, come up with a fancy treatment plan, and tell you to schedule more time to come back for a cleaning. Why would anyone go to the dentist for anything but a cleaning?\n\nWhen I moved away from the area, I specifically told the front desk not to make another appointment for me. Imagine my frustration when several months later I start receiving text reminders for an upcoming appointment, with warnings about a $50 no-show fee. I immediately texted back saying I never made that appointment and telling them to cancel it. I received another appointment reminder a week later and again texted back saying I did not make that appointment.\n\nNow, I have texted ~5 more times over the last 2 weeks asking for them to send my X-rays to my new dentist. I have not received a single text response since I stopped being a customer. I called and was told my X-rays would be sent by the end of the day, and they weren’t.\n\nThey’re friendly for as long as they can make money off you, and the moment they can’t, they go dark.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mikel Moore","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLpOPp8IBmdNHzdPic471zldWLA2GCkNcBzYOfmp0xlsu3XmA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Marmurek was thorough and provided an incredible patient experience!  In addition, the office environment was welcoming and an enjoyable place to be. I’m looking forward to my next cleaning.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
